    `},{id:"thm-1.2-gaps-rationals",title:"Theorem 1.2 (Gaps in Rationals)",statement:"Let $A = \\{p \\in \\mathbb{Q} : p > 0 \\text{ and } p^2 < 2\\}$ and $B = \\{p \\in \\mathbb{Q} : p > 0 \\text{ and } p^2 > 2\\}$. Then $A$ contains no largest element and $B$ contains no smallest element.",sectionId:0,sectionTitle:"Introduction",category:"Real Numbers",type:"theorem",hasProof:!0,proof:`
